# Testing

1. `pnpm build`
2. validate the package in a disposable cleanroom or containerized runtime
   first
3. `nex package validate .`
4. `nex package release .`
5. `nex package smoke . --frontdoor-origin <url> --frontdoor-api-token <token> --server-id <id>`

Use already-lived-in local or hosted runtimes only for secondary dogfood after
the cleanroom path passes.
